# Taskmaster Workflow

- **Session Start**
  - Begin by listing tasks and checking the next available item.
  - Inspect full task details before implementation.

- **Execution Loop**
  - For complex work, expand the task into subtasks first.
  - Set the active item to in-progress before coding.
  - Log implementation progress in subtask updates.

- **Status Hygiene**
  - Mark completed items as done immediately after validation.
  - Keep blocked work visible through accurate task status updates.
  - Update upcoming tasks when implementation decisions drift from plan.

- **Default Command Sequence**
  - `task-master list --with-subtasks`
  - `task-master next`
  - `task-master show <id>`
  - `task-master expand --id=<id> --research` (as needed)
  - `task-master update-subtask --id=<id> --prompt="<notes>"`
  - `task-master set-status --id=<id> --status=done`
